Package edu.harvard.hms.dbmi.bd2k.irct.model.query

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ClauseAbstract
    An abstract class that represents any clause that can be part of a query.
    JoinClause
    Creates a clause to support joins done on a remote resource
    JoinType  
    PredicateType
    The predicate type class provides a way for the IRCT application to keep track of which predicates can be used.
    Query
    The query class represents any query against any individual or group of resources.
    SelectClause
    The select clause provides a list of parameters and/or operations that should be returned by the query.
    SelectOperationType
    The select operation type class provides a way for the IRCT application to keep track of which select operations can be used.
    SortClause
    The sort clause provides a method to sort data that is to be returned by the query.
    SortOperationType
    The sort operation type class provides a way for the IRCT application to keep track of which select operations can be used.
    SubQuery
    A sub query may be part of a query or another sub query.
    WhereClause
    The where clause contains information used in a query to filter upon the data.
